,Recommended,290340,28096155,"Posted: 30 November, 2016",all,Panic Route ™,"+ 500 Hours. High time I did a review for ‘Armello.’ Here goes.Armello(Lets keep this brief)Armello is an adventure-strategy board game. Follow four heroes as they race for the throne of Armello, ruled by a corrupted king. There are basically four victory options. Prestige victory: gaining prestige from completing quests(unless you fail), killing banes(unless your corrupted)and heroes. Spirit Stone victory: banish the corrupted king using four spirit stones which you’ve gained through quests and stone circles. And finally, Kingslayer and Rot victory are very similar, you have to kill the king via combat and survive, when trying for Rot, your Rot needs to be higher than the king's.(Just play the game, the mechanics are engaging and easy to pick up.)Gameplay+ 4 different clan containing heroes with unique abilities(Always increasing variety of heroes)+ Hex tile design+ Day/Night cycle+ Huge replayability(+ 500 Hours in fact)+ Four victory options+ Interactive turn-based system+ Cards+ Story-driven prologue – including the tutorial. Really easy to understand and explains the game mechanics.o Multiplayer(host leave may crash the game)o Luck and random number generator(can be frustrating at times)Based on the games originality, artistic design and the games narrative style, has kept me hooked to this game for so long. With heroes moving on hex based tile, and trying to get prestige, magic, coins or even rot sometimes. Quest to increase your hero’s stats, whether that be towards Fight, Body, Wits or Spirit, all depends on your game play. The amount of strategy within this game is huge which adds to the replayability of Armello.Multiplayer, create a party or lone wolf against other competitive players, you decide. Host quit? Don’t worry, the games mechanics are good against leavers or delaying players and the AI’s still oppose quite a challenge, although, when the host drops it might result to game crash, with constant up-dates, the developers are working hard and fast to resolve this.Visual+ Amazing art style+ Animations(Including the cards – nice touch)+ Dices- Few graphic glitchesArmello is visually stunning, and with the addition of the new seasons DLC, each season has its own glorious allures. Also combat animations with dice rolls are amazing, differing whether the dice explodes or not, also hit to the hero differs from a blocked attack. There are still some graphic glitches, but very rare and doesn’t usually affect the gameplay.Soundtrack+ Stylised+ Lisa Gerrard performance+ Changing accordingly to the atmosphereSoundtrack is very well created and composed. Songs are underlining the dark-fantasy atmosphere and whilst also creating a place of serenity. Lisa Gerrard participated during the composure of the sound track, her voice well known from Dead Can Dance or Gladiator suits melodies, really adds to the music’s ambience. The soundtrack is also released and made available to all, including the non-early-access players.Story Time!(It’simportantfun to role-play)In game chat is disabled, this eliminates the possibility of players encountering toxic or hateful language, as this game is designed to suit players of all ages. However, the use of chat emotes allows players to communicate, regardless of their language, and to fully immerse oneself into the world of Armello, whilst retaining the character’s demeanour and tone.Furthermore, the developers are receptive to new idea and suggestions on how to expand and improve the current chat tree.With a little creatively, the current chat emotes can be used to forge alliances, taunt your enemies or simply express your characters emotions.Narrator:With the addition of Usurpers, 3 heroes’ gazed dumbstruck towards the castle, as a seemingly out of place bear, continued to idle around the castle battlements. Confused? Perhaps the bear was bewildered by his good fortune, or perhaps he shared the other heroes’ sentiment.Elyssia:Ow! That. Ow.Magna:No! I can’t believe it!Elyssia:Speechless.Narrator:The heroes’ stared in disbelief as the bear continued to marvel at his new heritageSargon:Ill fortune.Fate is fluid. This is but a minor setback.Elyssia:Who’s fault was that?!(Elyssia snapped, accusingly)Narrator:Resentment and bitterness blossomed between those whom had lost the race to the throne, however, despite the squabbling, carried the distant cries and whoops of delight.Ghor:Woooooaaaaaahhhhhh……..As King, will I ‘have’ to live in the palace?.Magna:I don’t want to be part of this.(Magna concluded, hefting her shield)Until we meet again!……….. To be continued!This is only one potential outcome, How will you play?!? Would you play fair? Or team up to crush those who oppose your claim to the throne. Strategy or luck, you decide, but a good player will always ensure that the odds are in their favour. This is going to be dramatic.(*Popcorn at the ready!*)Take a Hint!Hero’s traits, rings and amulets are extremely important in determining your play style during early game. An experienced player will also take tile advantages/disadvantages into account, as well as, the Day and night cycle also brings an important aspect to the game. Never attempt fate if you can help it, luck is a risk and can be terribly frustrating. Minimise the risk and ensure you equip item cards which best server your play style and repeatedly burn your cards to ensure you have the hand you want, remember, each card has a unique symbol – sword/shield/rot/wyld/sun and moon, burn these cards during combat or perils to ensure the outcome is in your favour.Finally, be sure to watch an opponent’s move:(Cannot express how important this it!)Money and Magic usage:  Is a good indicator of the sort of perils your up against.States and Equipped items: Will help indicate whether you need to play aggressively or defensively.The community!(It’s worth a mention)The game is constantly going through bug fixes. The community is always kept up-to-date with patches and with any new additional content to the game. The developers are very friendly and receptive to any great ideas found though the Amello community, that be through steam, facebook, twitter, youtube, twitch or the forums. Members of the community also show no lack of passion, creativity and empathy. However, this is only maintained thought the developers zero tolerance to hatred and discrimination. Overall, the community is very welcoming, just be respectful and mindful of your opinions as it could potential be harmful to others.Diagnosis!Infection, query sepsis ?!, Potentially infectious.Refer these animals to their GP; for a prescription of antibiotics.(Penicillin, Amoxicillin + Fluoroquinolones)My overall rating for Armello: 9/10 – Would put the King out of his misery again!Also got my vote for ‘Steam Awards Nomination 2016’ – Keep up the good work!On a final note, are the DLC’s worth paying for? Yes they are, the developers have never asked for anything, with free up-dates and content being constantly added to game, this is a way for us to help show our support. Armello is a truly inspiring game, let’s not lose it."
