,Recommended,290340,23463289,"Posted: 8 June, 2016",all,ChronosTC,"Oneshot, Mad King.That's all I need.This game is a board game with eight different playable characters, each with their own unique ability and two to a single Clan, and can be played with friends or against bots as you quest to become the king or queen of Armello.If you hate RNG, just avoid this game.The game is heavily RNG-based, but heroes' passive abilities do work quite well, and the difficulty of the four victories varies. Prestige is easiest while Rot is hardest in my own experience. My only problem with the game is that it has a severe reliance on praying to RNGesus that whatever is happening goes in your favor. I'm honestly writing a review way sooner than I should be (11.5 hours upon writing this review) but so far I enjoy the game.Definitely a 4/5 to me, one of the games that I feel deserves an attempt at one of my few serious reviews."
