,Recommended,290340,27650840,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,_Randi_,"If you like boardgames, or you just want to try a good one here on Steam, I suggest adding Armello to your wishlist.Here is a small list of the things I appreciate the most, that may help you decide if it's worth your interest:. different ways to win (adapt your strategy as you play). characters and stats modifiers (lot of combinations to experiment with). dice (in great quantity with nice skins and effects). cards (to equip, use or ""burn"" before dice rolls to mitigate results). missions (to upgrade your stats, get better equipment and find followers). rules alteration (game changes if you are corrupted or not). prestige points mechanic (if you have the most you can influence the game). hand management, area control, stealth mechanics. random board generation, great art and nice soundtrack. well... there is more, but I think you should experience it ;DI find in Armello a great variety of elements I enjoy, so I keep coming back for more. I like trying a different strategy everytime and the fact that other characters will be added, definitely keeps my interest high. You can't play it hotseat, but that's because some mechanics don't make it possible. Even if I'm not playing with friends, my online experience is totally fine (no one ever left the game or purposely made the game end faster). If you have problems finding opponents, just keep an eye for special events organized by the LoG devs. Have fun Armellians!"
