,Recommended,290340,31809566,Posted: 17 May,all,Carnifex,"This game never fails to relax me. It's my go-to game when I have that ""unmotivated sunday I don't know what to do"" feeling. It can get pretty intense and competitive though but all in a nice and well-handled manner.Firstly I really want to complement the artstyle, design concept and music.They all add a lot to the atmosphere! The artstyle for characters and the landscape look really smooth and cute, kinda like a fairytale, but as soon as you are ingame you will find out that there is a dark twist.The whole setting and music are really calm. The design of the cards is really gorgeous and I like that the cards also feature the artists signature.Secondly the game concept is a lot of fun and simple! It's basically a boardgame rpg where you have one goal: Be the new King or Queen of Armello. There are 4 different ways to achieve this and there are also 4 players on the field.Different stats, abilities, starting boosts and cards add a big variety to how you can pursue this goal.Especially the cards offer a lot of utility when it comes to giving yourself some boosts or hinder your opponents.There are 3 types of cards: items, magic and trickery.All the characters exel in different aspects and the cards can help you to improve your strengths or minimize your weaknesses.Thirdly, and this is really important to me: This game and people are not toxic!They can't be toxic because there is no ingame chat! I love this option and i think this adds a lot to the game.You can use predetermined phrases to express some basic emotions and react to or show what you feel about different actions ingame.It is turn based which makes the pace of the game pretty slow but that is nothing bad in my opinion. Near the end of the game it's getting pretty intense when everyone is trying to go for the king and claim his throne.The only thing that bothers me sometimes is that magic and wits seem like the most viable stats. It is nothing crazy or something that i would call broken, but it gives the most utility which is a big factor in this game. A high wits stat enables you to draw a lot of cards and a high magic stat gives you the power to use more or stronger magic cards.I rarely use the trickery cards which is a shame in my opinion but maybe that is just because of my character preference.There are 2 character dlc packs which increase the number of playable characters by 8 in total. (So double the included characters). They add some nice new strategies to play with them because of their abilities but nothing that doesn't fit into the game or makes the balance an issue. The standard characters are really enough if you want to enjoy the game, but the dlc's can add some diversity and freshness. I feel like no character really stands out to be particularly stronger than the others.Lastly I want to talk about the ""drop system"" in this game.After every game you can either get a chest or a key (The chance for each seems to be 1/2, so it's super fair. (I applaude for this because i have never seen someone add KEYS as drops so you don't actually have to spend money)From the chests you can get new die to throw at your enemies faces when you end up in a battle with them.I strongly recommend this game and if you feel like it's something for you, it's definitely worth it!The wonderful artstyle combined with the rpg and tabletop elements and non-toxicity really make this game a place I love to come back to!"
