76561198164405631,Recommended,290340,17851084,"Posted: 2 September, 2015",all,FloxDutch,"I've played quite a lot while this game was in early-acces and finally decided to create a review since it's just fully released. So here's my quick review :DPros:- A lot of strategy: There is a time limit of around 1.5 minute online per turn. You really need this time to complete your turn properly. Every move is a decision.- Great artwork: The game just looks absolutely amazing. Especially the cartoonish artwork in the 'fight scenes'.- RNG: The game works with random cards you get in your hand, this makes every match a different experience. The fight system works with dices, so you can get lucky or very unlucky, but overall, the player with the best odds wins most of the battles.The RNG part is something you may or may not like. I personally liked the RNG part, because the winner of the match is still mostly decided by skill, not RNG.Cons:- Slow: In an online game you are waiting most of the time. This isn't that much of a problem since you can still play cards while it's not your turn, but still, one game takes about one hour.- Matchmaking: Getting into an online match can take some time.EDIT: As of now, the wait timers are very reasonable.Overall this game is worth your money if you like Strategy games and can enjoy the RNG parts."
