76561198030935069,Recommended,290340,17341304,"Posted: 1 August, 2015",all,sdbishop1221,"I grabbed this game last minute in early access, and I'm glad I did.  Quick rundown:The world of Armello itself looks great and feels very alive already, even though I've been playing for only a few days.  I'd love to see something like a single player story mode for each character in the full release or down the road, because I feel like the characters have strong potential for development.  That would also expand the gameplay possibilities in single player.As for the gameplay specifically, it seems complicated at first, but it doesn't take long to pick up.  There are tool tips everywhere, so you can figure out everything on your own at your own pace.  I also believe tutorials will be added for the full game.  That should help.I see just a couple drawbacks in the game right now.  First, it seems the A.I. is a bit overwhelmed by it all.  Once you have the basics down, it's clear that if you come in with a specific victory in mind, it's not too difficult to win a single player game.  With just one difficulty level, there's no scalability to the challenge; once you've figured out how to win, you routinely beat the computer.Second, it's hard to find a multiplayer game at the moment, but that's an easy fix as long as the userbase expands on full release.Those concerns aside, I'm quite impressed with this game, and it should only improve as it leaves early access."
