76561198025059659,Recommended,290340,23010423,"Posted: 15 May, 2016",all,Tovlyn,"An amazing production all around.The art direction is beautiful, filled with animations and visually pleasing graphics.The soundtrack is very atmospheric and blends seamlessly with the games' many soundeffects.And the story, though tragic is equally powerful and immersive as both the visuals and the music.The gameplay itself is rewarding in every sense of the word, with things like microrewards just for participating in games, and a myriad of other ways to keep hope lit during a particularly unlucky streak. There's incredible potential for variety in every match, and no game is the other alike. In this game the pen and the sword are equally matched, and with the 4 alternate ways of achieving victory they ensure that every turn can twist the game in a new direction.At first it may feel a bit slow, because each turn takes a fair bit of time. But since there's little restrictions with what cards can be played on other people's turns, you quickly learn how to not only speed that wait up, but keep yourself busy during it.As with any game boasting this much variety between every match, luck can of course also become an obstacle. But in those scenarios you learn how to deal around it. Either by seeking an alternate path or just bide your time until another presents itself. Many games have been turned around completely by attentive underdogs who knew how to play their cards right.The multiplayer has also lived up to expectations. Swift game lobbies and amusing phrases exhanged between players doing their best to add more surprises to the game helps renewing gameplay even further. Once you feel confident enough to try it out I can wholeheartedly recommend it, with random players or friends.I can tell that a lot of effort was put into this game, and it took me completely by surprise just how well thought through it is in just about every single aspect.I sincerely recommend this game to pretty much anyone, either as a fun way to pass some time or a challenge for those who enjoy competition with other players. I'd give this game a 9/10."
