76561197991567851,Recommended,290340,18025907,"Posted: 13 September, 2015",all,Fixxed,"An addicting and amazing boardgame with a relatively steep learning curve.The game has an amazing vibe, good compelling dynamics and is beautifully, masterfully crafted in order to make RNG not only competitive but not that frustrating!!So to explain how they did that (or why I believe they did) I must first say that, I bought this game as a boardgame designer, to understand some really interesting peculiarities.It is imbedded in RNG and as far as transparency goes, this game is not an example. So is it bad? No...As a strong believer in pre-production and heavy design in order to combat rng and give space to balance and skill, this game showed me new possibilities for luck and uses it in a way that hasnt really been seen in Boardgames before.Most decisions in the game, involve luck ( % ), however, it is post luck, as in, first macro decisions (where you go, what you do and so on) then micro decisions that will have luck mechanic. To illustrate: you gear your character, move him on the map and decide whether you want to engage in luck events or not. IF you do, then your gear, character info (relative to race, buffs, etc) shall weigh the outcome of the event, may it be a battle or some other encounter.So luck serves as a weight to your moves in order to make the game more competitive and dense Strategically wise.Furthermore, the game uses really amazing Aesthetics to brush off unecessary intensity and soothe your experience, as a hot soup blow. So when rng does get on your nerves, you will barely notice it over the amazing music, illustrations and whole experience.The only con to the game, is the amount of info you must attend to simultaneously. Meaning that, while it does have a good UI, it uses the fact it is a digital boardgame, to incert more information than anyone could possibly process. PLus, the learning curve is indeed steep and although tutorial process is connected storywise, it is still a dull process....All in all, this game is really really good and worth cutting through the tough leathery learning membrane.Online games are really intense but still manage to maintain the shoothing game's vibe. 8/10"
