76561198077533629,Recommended,290340,17909747,"Posted: 6 September, 2015",all,foxdevil1,"The only bad thing I could ever say, even after playing this game for several hours now, and enjoying the liveing bejesus out of it, is that I didnt know about it's kickstarter. I would have been dumping money into this.Aside from 'shut up and take my money', I suppose I shoulld give some actual details on the game.Its a board game, where the premis is simple. Become king/queen. Your competeing with three other heros and the current king himself at times, to do just that. The way you go about playing is all up to you. Do you build up your character before walking right up to the king and kill him man to man? Or do you politicaly bide your time, gaining the king's favor and eventualy when he dies, the crown.The board on wich you play is new every time. This coupled with the fact that there are eight characters currently (supposivly more in the future) means that each game can be entirely diffrent. I look forward to seeing what they do with this game.A note to the devs if only for the giggles, a playable vulpine character of any sort. Seriously, I will chuck money at that if I have to. I'm already bummed I missed the chance to support your kickstarter."
