,Recommended,290340,18076852,"Posted: 17 September, 2015",all,Wildeflit,"4 ways to win, 8 characters(I hear more are coming, like Squirrels) with their own bonuses and only takes around 30 minutes for a full game.  I love how you can customize to set yourself up, but then the little bit of randomness in each of the three decks of cards (you choose which you draw from) can totally change your strategy.""I just need one more Spirit for this Teleport"" ""This ally makes my spells cheaper"" ""A staff that gives me prestige for holding towns?"" ""Shoot 2 points of rot right off the bat I guess I should try for the Rot Victory"" ""Oh a spirit stone appeared right beside me, maybe I should collect them""  ""I can box him in with Perils..."" These are the kind of things you'll be saying.  There is a large element of luck, but a lot of it is playing(or finding ways to get rid of) your cards well and the game can quickly change right up to the end.A wonderful race of guts and glory, my new GOTO game when I don't have a ton of time to sink."
,Recommended,290340,17944444,"Posted: 8 September, 2015",all,Gerg,"Surprisingly rich and complex boardgame brought to the PC in a really beautiful way. There is a surprisingly depth to Armello, for each of the characters, that would make this game terrible to play on a tabletop, but as a digital boardgame it excels -- impressive!There is a fair bit of cartoon violence and intercharacter conflict... which is to say, murdering your fellow players is an effective and often necessary strategy -- friendships beware. Death is only a minor setback, and may be beneficial in many cases, though.The art style is beautiful and accentuates the background story and keeps every turn engaging. Attack animations, unique touches for the characters, and wonderful card art (and animation!) are all top notch. If you're curious, investigate how they incentivized art contributions!There are a few bugs: things like chunks of the interface that can go missing, but for the most part, resetting resolution or alt-tabbing can fix that. Full-screen functionality (Command+F) on Mac seems to be wonky, but works most of the time. There are some sound issues.Game balance is pretty well done. Rot seems hard to collect, but that's about the extent of it. Some folks complain about River sniping the king, but to them I say, kill the Wolf! Would love to see better error-handling in the netcode, as there is no way to get a player that disconnected back into the game; they're replaced by a hot.Note that the game is MUCH improved by playing with real players. The AI is a little on the simple side and tends to go all out to fixate on a specific character each game -- often the player. You can't argue with AI, and the minor metagame of diplomacy does improve the experience."
,Recommended,290340,17952672,"Posted: 8 September, 2015",all,Vasmir,"I have enjoyed this game, the art style, gameplay and over all idea if pretty fun. I would give it a 7/10 though, few reason which I'll give below.Pros:-Lovely Art Style-Interesting play style of the old hexagon rpg table tops-Animations are well done and fluid-Concept of the game is imagnitive-Multiplayer works well and tests your friendships (Who will help you or end you)-Interesting Game mechanics, from complete dice modification, to in game affect through choices.-Loveable and cute characters: I mean look a Barneby, He's so damn eager to bonk them.Cons:-No game customization (You can't alter your map experience, each map is rerolled at a set size. Ways to fix this would be allow an option of multiple map sizes, with other game alterations)-Winning is single minded: You win by having the highest prestige, whether or not you have slayed the king or not. (Ways to fix this, Make prestige victory a draw breaker [both player and king die or king dies without a killing blow being dealt] I beleive the game could have alternative ways to win as well, fix the king, remove the rot from him, corrupt him fully, etc)-Restricted Character: The block on the additional bandit clan almost made me not buy this, and some of my friends refunded because of this. This is a good way to hurt player base when you have a purchasable game with locked characters, if the game was FTP then it would be understandable, or if they were purchasable from a DLC (Which would be a good idea for future clans as well, or adding them in as free updates)-Short: This game is short, if you don't love it, you'll get bored quickly.The map is as big as a small continent from Sid meiser's Civ games. Quests only go to about 5 or 6 (haven't counted persoanlly) before you get end game quest."
