76561198038596718,Recommended,290340,14184401,"Posted: 26 January, 2015",all,cemery756,"I was extremely attracted to this game because it immediately reminded me of the Redwall book series I loved as a kid. Bought it on sale for a rather steep $20... still not sure if it was worth it (only time will tell), but I can say that the game is fun and well-designed.Pros:Despite having very little in the way of a tutorial, I found the rules and mechanics pretty easy to grasp after a couple quick test runs. The interface and controls are quite intuitive.Playing as most characters (see more on this below...), the game's difficulty seems well balanced, not too hard and not too easy. This is due in part to the fact that luck does play a role in whether you win or lose any given battle/situation, but I see this as a positive rather than a negative. Your skill is still what wins you the game in the end.Nice art design, graphics, music, and overall theme.The game rewards you for playing and achieving different paths to victory, with unlockable perks for each character.Cons:Could use more content, more maps, maybe a campaign of some sort...The story is superficial and leaves a bit to be desired. This is also something that a campaign mode with cutscenes would help fix.One of the playable characters, the bear, seems to always lose really badly when played by the AI. I haven't tried playing her yet but there's obviously a bit of an imbalance there."
