76561198023345422,Not Recommended,290340,29710063,Posted: 4 February,all,Eldric,"This game had potential, but unfortunately, while the general concept is good - it just doesn't live up to what it COULD be.Went into this game thinking ""Oh hey, it's based on tabletop RPGs - I've played those before and they can be entertaining, going through dungeons in a group, questing, etc. Sure, I'll give it a shot!"" but alas, it wasn't meant to be...There is absolutely nothing in this game that ""sucks you in"" in terms of gameplay. The ENTIRE time you're playing, you're staring at a tiny little map broken up into hexes, with giant figures featuring you, the three opponent ""player"" AI, and various other AI representing the King's guards, Rot enemies, etc. all moving around....but that's it in terms of gameplay. Want to quest in a dungeon - just step on a dungeon hex! But that's all you end up doing - after that your reward is randomly generated or you could trigger one of the Rot NPCs....you don't get to go through an actual dungeon, quest, deal with monsters, find treasure, etc. like you would in a tabletop RPG. Nope, you just step on a tile and the system randomly rewards (or penalizes) you.Want to explore a town, maybe do a quest? Yeaaah....no. Not gonna happen. Once again, step on a tile, a quest pops up - you gotta roll dice or burn cards with symbols on them (seriously?) to somehow ""win"" the quest. Fail - penalized, win - oh boy, you get a few coins or maybe a card...Want to buy equipment or upgrade your pre-existing? Nope - you gotta somehow hope that you pick an item card (when that finally happens in the game) that fits what your need, if not, you're stuck with a card for a piece of equipment you don't want.No, the entire time you're playing this game, you're staring at a hex map. Want to start a party - maybe quest some? Nope, not here. A ""party"" are basically npcs you win through questing - and we've already talked about questing. They're basically cards that hardly ever interact (if at all) with you and just provide a modicum of points/benefits (if any) for you.This entire game is nothing more than numbers chasing - you're trying to become the Prestige leader for every turn, trying to acquire 4 soul stones to MAYBE heal the Lion King, trying to gain enough corruption/hit points to take ON the King in combat, etc. Meantime, the other npc players are trying to handicap you at every turn, laying traps, stealing your money, attacking you, etc.Needless to say, this got boring FAST.Listen, this game is basically eye-candy and even then - not much else. Plotwise - it's got about as much depth as a kiddie pool with a half-inch of water in it. The storyline is the barest boned I've seen in a LONG time. You never really explore this world - you just wander through it, trying to get your character high enough before the game times out or is won by someone else. Game mechanics are pretty much luck based, and if there's something along the lines of actual strategy involved - I've yet to see that.This game had the potential to be SO much more. Given the types of similar ""anthropomorphized animals in a medieval/magic-based setting"" content out there - such as the Autumnlands and Mouse Guard comics, plus pre-existing RPG games that follow D&D mechanics, such as Might & Magic, this game could've been more immersive, more plot driven, so much more INTERESTING than it currently is! Where are the quests to try and find out more about ""The Rot""? Where are the quests to explore the history of this land? Where are the quests to explore the land, PERIOD!?!? I'd have loved to be able to put together a party of npc characters or even multiplayer friends, and just QUEST in a dungeon or explore the wilds of this kingdom, fighting monsters, doing quests, etc. instead of running around like crazy people, from one end of the map to the other, trying to perform what comes down to as MEANINGLESS quests, all in an effort to numberchase against AI opponents...This isn't entertainment, it's very pretty annoyance and monotony. And yes, much like everybody else, I find it appalling that there's FURTHER in-game purchases for what is nothing more than variations of the same eyecandy skins that already comes with the game, and very little of anything else. The fact that they charge almost (if not more) for the ""upgrades"" than the game itself make me scratch my head in wonder as WHY someone would continue to fork out money for a game to look remotely prettier if the game mechanics are (at the end of the day) still pretty damn boring.My recommendation - Avoid Like the PLAGUE!"
