76561197998495342,Recommended,290340,19819082,"Posted: 20 December, 2015",all,wolflahti,"Armello has been aptly described as a ""virtual boardgame"". You play against other folks online or against computer opponents, on a rather small but artfully rendered map, with the goal of becoming leader of the kingdom in one of four ways. You increase your stats by completing quests, defeating other players (or evil critters known as banes) in battle, or by luck of the draw from a deck of cards. Cards can grant you bonuses, temporary or otherwise, or you can play disadventageous cards on your enemies. Cards can also be ""burned"" (exchanged for a sure roll on your dice) in battle.While strategy has a decided effect on the outcome of a game, sometimes there is nothing you can do against a bad run of luck, and that is my only real complaint - too much luck is involved in gameplay, what with the cards, the dice rolls, and the arbitrary appearance of the quests and perils. I won my very first game almost purely by luck, because I really had no idea what I was doing.Despite this, I find Armello enjoyable and well worth the cost. It will appeal mostly to people who enjoy board games, but others may find it engaging as well."
