76561198049376196,Recommended,290340,20927170,"Posted: 2 February, 2016",all,ClubfootandtheWarlock,"A fantastical world that brings childhood novels like Redwall to life! Be an animal, roll all the dice you ever wanted, gain a rot dice that undoes some of those dice; equip a weapon card to add more dice, or ""burn"" the item to auto-lock the particular side you want. Watch as chance sends you home or displays the prowess of your chosen totem animal waving a weapon in the manner which symbolizes victory! Swash Swish! Dice! Health leftover? No? You die too! Find a way to make htis happen to the King without dying in the process, or find glowy blue orbs, or become corrupted, so much replayability that you may not uncover a particular victory condition until your fourth or fifth play through of this digitalized board game.Ever wanted to save the kingdom from a were-liger (lion-tiger)?Would you rather be the rat that cashes in on espionage skulking about in the shadows of village hexes, or who goes all out in night-time ambushes, with the other players losing track of you every other turn and fearing to move too far towards you?Perhaps you prefer the tank-bears, skilled in cleansing the land of the were-liger's shadow raven monsters, or the other bear tank that gains attack for using spells (Which themselves are quite lethal, or have utility like teleporting or healing).Would you rather chance it on the cards and get up close and personal, or damage weakened foes from range, either way the wolf clan can satisy the umame flavours of combat.The rabbit clan are cowards. Heavily armored and adventurous, they luck out and win sometimes, but usually thep layers can spite them to death as they gain bonuses from going into pits and emerging with armfuls of unique treasures (which the other clans have a slightly lower chance to gain in this particular hex), or gianing bonuses to armor."
