,Recommended,290340,18350025,"Posted: 5 October, 2015",all,๖ۣۜKawaii NeeTz,"Love this game to death with a nice community and a lovely game. There are some quirks to it but that's quickly overshadowed by all the fun you have playing the game. For starters:This is a turned based game that has a lot of cool mechanics which are and are not limited to:Mana usage - Cast spells on opponents during your turn and on someone elses turn (can't target players that is taking their turn)Money usage - Funds the perils and trickery cards which turn the battle for Armello in your favorPerils which are trapsDifferent character types and abilities for each of the clans united by the KingA generator map that is different everytime you play it.This game is really fun but the core of the game is how you're suppose to win. There are 4 ways of winning the game.1. Win by Prestige. Most common winning method by my experience. You pretty much do good deeds and kill enemy heroes and banes. You can also complete the quests.2. Win by King Kill. Go into the Palace and kill the king to win the game!3. Win by Spirit Stone. After stepping into the Palace, you can win instantly by exiling the king.4. Win by Rot. Compete against the King to whoever is the most corrupted. You gain additonal die for having a higher rot score.There are different ways of playing the game, but why don't you buy it and try it yourself? It's 20 bucks and well worth the amount of money being put into the game."
