,Recommended,290340,27910754,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,ＲＥＯＮＡＲＤ,"""Dovie'andi se tovya sagain.""It's time to toss the dice.Being a lover of fantasy, roleplaying, anthropomorphismNo, I am not a Furry, trickery, and dumb luck, I decided to buy this game. I have not regretted it. I was a little lost starting off, but after a few matches I started to pick up all the intricacies of the game better, and now I only improve the more I play.In this game, you select a Hero or Heroine of one of the Five Clans: Wolf, Bear, Rabbit, Rat, and Bandit. Your quest? Save the kingdom of Armello from the careless rule of a once-good King overcome by the Rot, an all-consuming corruption that has tragically driven him into spiraling madness. You must become the new King or Queen of Armello bywhatever means necessary,be it alliance, betrayal, fame, daring acts of heroism, or, if you so choose, by becoming even more powerful in the Rot than the Mad King himself.Like I said, this game relies heavily on RNG, which is (as far as I know) essentially a technical term among RPGers for blind, dumb luck. Most of your strategy comes from leveling up certain stats, thereby increasing your ""luckiness"", and by playing cards to other players and to different tiles. You can win three different ways. The first is a Prestige Victory, where the Hero or Heroine with the most ""Prestige"" becomes the new ruler of Armello after the King perishes (he is slowly dying) by right of succession. The other two methods are much more direct: Kingslayer and Spirit Stone Victories. Kingslayer is exactly what it sounds like: you confront the Mad King and defeat him in combat. A Spirit Stone Victory is the trickiest, but I believe it is the most satisfying. You collect four of these objects called ""Spirit Stones"", holy objects of great power, that crystallize randomly at Stone Circle tiles across the board. You then confront the King and use their power to banish him. There is also a Rot Victory, though I consider it to be one and the same with a Kingslayer Victory, but of course with the added detail of your Rot exceeing that of the King.Getting into the Palace is usually the hardest part. Everyone has their eyes on it, so everyone wants to keep you from reaching it.I have yet to try Multiplayer in Armello, but from what I've heard, it is much more fun with friends than with strangers.So, if you like politcal intrigue, fantasy, animals, and tabletop RPGs, get this game. You may want to wait until a sale to purchase it, though. That's what I did.As for the DLCs, I have not yet purchased them, but I do plan on doing so. The added characters look fun to play as, and the aesthetic pack looks good, as well. But once again, you should probably wait for a sale.I give this game a 10/10.EDIT:I just bought Usurpers, and the characters seem pretty balanced. I recommend getting it, but, again, wait until a sale. Now I just have to hold my breath for the Bandit Clan DLC...EDIT 2:Multiplayer and the community are great! I've played with both cutthroat and nice gamers, and the matches can get very intense and competitve.A forewarning: some players have a highly developed sense of vengeance. Messing with them once may make you their nemesis for the remainder of the match.EDIT 3:Okay, I admit the games can run a little slow in multiplayer, but I still enjoy them. Just make sure you have an hour or two cleared--no one ever said tabletop gaming was quick.EDIT 4:I highly enjoy all four of the Bandit Clan characters, and recommend purchasing the DLC. A wealth of content for just $10.Like my review? Check out myCuratorpage!"
,Recommended,290340,23029339,"Posted: 16 May, 2016",all,Ghost powerplant,"A fine board game video game.Fight your friends to become king. You spend time walking around a board game getting loot and spells and traps to murder/steal/scheme against your friends so you can be the next king when he dies.2hr~ game time.  Lots of RNG but its very manageable if you play smart. If a random element doesn't bother you and you are capable of setting aside large chunks of time for this game, I highly reccomend it."
,Recommended,290340,23062830,"Posted: 18 May, 2016",all,SpaceYeti,"Interesting table-top styled strategy game. The gameplay is largely dice and card-draw based, meaning there is a lot of RNG. Where the game shines is in how strategy emerges in how you manage the RNG through burning cards, building your character, and understanding what your opponents are doing. As such, while there is still a good deal of RNG, good players are the ones who know how to control and bias the randomness in their favor.There are 4 ways to win the game, but not each approach is on equal footing. The Prestige and Combat victories are by far the easiest, while the Spirit Stone victory trails a little behind. The Corruption victory is very difficult, and in many ways seems redundant to the Combat approach, which is far easier. That being said, the game is in continuing development, and I'm anticipating that as new heroes and cards are added to the game (in free updates and DLCs) that the depth and balance between different strategic approaches will be improved.TL; DR --- Do you like table-top games? Do you like turn-based strategy? Do you like games that have multiple ways to acheive victory? Do you have a brain for understanding RNG and managing it toward your favor? If you answered ""YES"" to all of these, buy this game. You wont regret it."
