,Recommended,290340,34561844,Posted: 28 August,all,Miju 水,"I picked this game up while it was on sale, I had initially played for free.In it's current state I can't recommend it for it's $20 asking price. I will throw that out there now, if some of it's issues get fixed I'd be willing to edit this review.I love this game, if you are a fan of games like 100% Orange Juice it feels fairly similar however feels more skill focused over RNG. Do not be mistaken, this game is HEAVILLY based on random number generation.Pros:- Well animated- Runs well on a low spec computer, while retaining quality- Fun, especially with friends- Big cast of characters all feel pretty unique- Lots of cards/questsNeutral:- There's a precomposed message system. Based on who you're playing you have a variety of different messages to communicate the same point. This of course is to limit the ammount of salt and toxicity to your game, which I believe in any RNG game there is bound to be. People will get mad. However, I think this is a GOOD choice.- Microtransactions/skins/loot the sheer fact that this would even be in a game will make people mad, however I've seen people call this game Pay2Win and that just isn't true in the slightest. Anything you can buy is on the marketplace, and none of it (aside from DLC characters which really aren't any more or less broken than the vanilla characters.) Plus you get drops after every game with a chance of a key or a chest. Do not buy ANYTHING from skeeve's store, buy on the marketplace the chests are seriously like 8 cents and the keys are 18. If nothing else, just keep selling your chests and buy the die you want from the marketplace.Cons:- 4 win conditions, but 3 are basically the same thing. (Kill the king, fight the king with 4 spirit stones, kill the king with higher rot.)- RNG (Often more of a negative than a positive in my experience.)- One map (I think the locations etc change but the map is still the same.)- Quests (There is no way to be able to predict where the next quest will be, but 90% of the time is the furthest it could possibly be from you.)- The AI seems RNG as well (When a player drops out AI takes over and does some of the dumbest♥♥♥♥♥♥imaginable. Often times suiciding to the king while killing him to give highest prestiege the winner cause why not.)and last but not least the biggest issue with the game.- Disconnect Issue/Intentional Infinite Turn GriefingI don't know what the problem is with this but in the last 6 games it's happened twice. Either a player disconnected and the game doesn't process it or they sit in their turn infinitely frozen at the drawing cards screen. This can be used to grief players into waiting and disconnecting without ANY means to skip their turn. Whether a bug or intentional it only stops when the player whos turn it is disconnects often resulting in games taking WAY too long and often making everyone else leave as well. Players leaving is already an issue with this game, and this on top of it makes it all the worse.I want to leave it recommended if it is on sale because I have had a BLAST playing with my friends. However, in the current I couldn't justify a $20 purchase. There is simply not enough content to warrant it. I almost don't want to recommend it for anything more than free as long as that disconnection grief exists, I hope they do something about this soon because I really want more people to play and enjoy this game."
