,Recommended,290340,23175832,"Posted: 23 May, 2016",all,wickdlowki,"# 53      ArmelloA board game set in a fantastical world  where animals are the dominant species, and a sickness called the rot ravages your King.  Adding cards, perils and board stylings of Catan, this board style game is actually a pretty slick joy.  Its a bit faster paced than Talisman, and way more polished.  One game ran me about an hour to play on single player, which is pretty fair for this type pf game.  The visuals are beautiful, smooth and well drawn, easy on the eyes.  And the sounds and music are very easy on the ears.At first glance the mechanics seem daunting, with a steep learning curve.  Not that way at all.  The tutorial is set up into 4 chapters, highlighting 4 of the 8 or so clans.  Each one adding a few new mechanics, until finally you learn about how to win the game.  Like i said, smooth.  Developers seem pretty active, having a twitch stream after each new update, highlighting the new features.I was a little peeved at the price, but after sitting down with it for a few hours, 20 bucks is actually pretty fair.8/10 might buy a copy for the spouse"
