,Recommended,290340,23077499,"Posted: 19 May, 2016",all,Randy Marsh [OpenSUSE TW],"Okay, I wrote a full-length review only to see it fail to post and I copied something else which removed my entry from clipboard to fml...Anyway, this game is not quite what I was expecting. It's also made from an Aussie studio which is awesome!This game is great. The art is nice, graphics are pretty. The audio (sound and music) are superb. The gameplay is fun, deep yet intuitive with different tactics/strats. It has high replayability and great for online play. You can also customise the rules online/offline to play however you like.Now the negatives. The game lacks some content, it's not an expensive game, it's actually quite cheap but for $20USD I'd like more than 1 level or at least some content for us solo players like a short campaign with a basic storyline. More characters and amulets/rings would be nice too, or at least more of the former. I'd also like a better matchmaking system with more detail and selections like choosing a public lobby. The prestige victory is also like the only worthy strat in most cases, this isn't a big deal as maybe it's supposed to be that way but the Rot victory is so hard to get, I got it on my 2nd day, but with AI, on PS4 only 0.8% of all players achieve a Rot victory and about 5.5% on Steam. The game does rely on skill and thoughtful strategies to win, however it's quite RNG dependent too, moreso than Hearthstone...but that's a bad example...I'd say slightly more than Chaos Reborn or at least on par.It sounds like there's more negatives, and there probably are more negatives, but they're quite small specific aspects. Don't worry, it wasn't a tough decision between a Yes/No for my recommendation. It was an easy ""Yes."" Don't buy it though if you don't like a little RNG, or boardgame/dice/card-type games with heavy multiplayer aspect and only 1 map. I'll now explain how the game works and go into some more detail (unfortunately my last unsaved review was way more in-depth and of clarity but this will make do). Also, I'd just like to quickly add that if this review made you or helped your purchase the game (or avoid it) give it a thumbs up or add me for some multiplayer goodness. I can also teach you the game! :) I'm really friendly and looking for friends. I'm an Aussie and have Skype and can download other software, I prefer using Discord though. Or we don't have to talk at all.It's a board game, where the object of the game is to succeed the king who is dieing from his infection by either slaying him, banishing with 4 spirit stones you collected or having the most prestige when he passes.The most common method of winning and the default (when time runs out) is a prestige win. The king suffers 1dmg each dawn, which is the same as what happen when you're infected with Rot. Although the infection can benefit or hamper you depending on your strategy, although I love playing for Rot/slay victory it's quite difficult and an all-or-nothing strat that often fails.You pick a character with a unique skill/ability, and a unique ring and amulet which give bonus stats. Then you start of with 3 AP (action points) to move 1 adjacent tile. There are different types of tiles which have different effects upon landing. Anyway, in fights, you roll dice which are determined by how much ""fight"" your character has, and in perils (like challenges to match symbols or traps) you roll your wit count and burn cards to win. Each cycle (dawn/night) you also draw cards up to the amount of Wits you have. You can choose from 3 decks which are equipment, spells/magic and trickery You can earn gold via settlements which is mostly used to play trap or equipment cards. And each night your magic fills up to how much Spirit you have and is used for magic/spell cards.So that's pretty much it for the basic outline of the game, it's a board game involving a lot of RNG (dice) and playing cards. It's also pretty fun, quite polished, and very fun to play with friends but I just wish it had more solo content (I love these types of games like Chaos Reborn, Armello and Hand of Fate which is also an Aussie game btw) or at least a way to join certain public lobbies rather than just search the queue and invite friends."
