,Recommended,290340,21722312,"Posted: 8 March, 2016",all,King Kranium,"I read some reviews before buying this game that were a bit misleading, so mostly I'm writing this to clear up some misconceptions you may have about this game. (I haven't touched multiplayer yet, so I'll be leaving that out)First off, this game is awesome. Fairly simple, easy to get into, and from what I've seen of the dev's website, continually updated. A single game on the default settings usually take 30-45 minutes to complete. You have the choice of eight different characters to play as and two different maps. You also have the option to equip one ring and one accessory that up different stats from the beginning of a game.You never know what's going to happen in a game, and you may even set out to win in one way, but end up on a different path later on. The card system adds a very deep layer to the gameplay, especially since you can play cards during other players' turns. Maps do seem small, but the way the map is used with quests and different terrains makes it feel a whole lot bigger.If you like turn-based games, get this. If you like card games, get this. If you like RPGs, get this. This game has all that and more for the very reasonable price of $20. Just buy it man, it's awesome."
