,Recommended,290340,29177956,Posted: 10 January,all,SlyFrost,"This game is pretty well built for a board game and has a ton of interesting features for gameplay! I love the animations and everything seems pretty streamline. I think there are still a few kinks to work out of course, but overall this is a pretty polisdhed product.Sometimes the game will hiccup, and I noticed multiple sound files would glitch and the right channel would go dead. Other than that, everything ran smooth. This may be due to hardware, but I have a relatively good setup and it should have no issues.The only cons I can say about this game is that it isn't really friendly to new players. The AI can get sort of ruthless, and you can definitely tell the computer has a plan, and will stick to it till you fail. There was a time where I took over a city, and the bear character attacked me three times in a row. It's possible, except for the fact that I destroyed him the first two times, (thanks to the lucky dice rolls, which is another problem I would like to get into) and on the last, the computer had enough and just killed me.As mentioned, this game is mostly chance. The only skill that is required of you is map movement, everything else is chance. Whether it be random♥♥♥♥♥spawning of enemies, or the cursed dice doing their thing. I sort of whish it was something more skill based than chance base. Sure, you can enforce strategies into the game, but they are so built on the chance factor (which often seems to be a 75% lodr 25% win ratio most times) that the strategies often fall apart.TL;DRGreat game, with some minor polishing that needs to be done, and gameplay relies too much on chance."
76561198080512687,Recommended,290340,29192243,Posted: 11 January,all,Raging Rooster,"Despite mostly positive reviews, I have to admit I wasn't too sure about buying the game at first. Most people that reviewed the game negatively, seemed to dislike the apparent long waiting times in matches (and as such long matches) and the general randomness. It put me off a little. I did put the game on my wishlist and I noticed I kept checking it out every day. So what the heck, I took the plunge.After getting a few games under my belt I can safely say: I do not regret buying it.The game looks great and plays exactly like a tabletop game should play. Not entirely sure how to explain it, but it has that feel to it. The amount of time you spend waiting for other players is very manageable; I never felt like I wanted to do something else while waiting. Matches take about an hour or so, give or take, which to me is perfect. And the randomness, well.. it's a dice-game.. It seems silly to complain about it (you don't complain about a RL game of Risk, or similar, I'd imagine) and there are plenty of ways to build your character as well as influence the game and other players by your actions. There's luck, and there's bad luck, but I always felt ""in control"".The lack of a regular chat system seemed odd at first, and at times I do miss it still, but the preset phrases you can hurl at eachother seem to cover most bases, and I can see the point in that it keeps things friendly. No salt or toxic nerdrage to feast your eyes upon. Being thick-skinned, a mute button would have been enough for me, but we have what we have, and it's fine.There's the odd quitter here and there, and it's difficult to determine if they quit intentionally or by accident. I've had one game lock up on me after 3 people subsequently dropped. Not sure what happened there, but it seems to be something that's around for a while already. I really hope it's not a too common occurrence; I don't mind losing a game, but getting a big ""nope! - you just wasted nearly an hour of your time"" simply sucks.All in all, solid 8,5/10 for the game, well done! If you're on the fence for the same reasons as me, don't hesitate to give the game a try."
