76561198043590223,Recommended,290340,34476457,Posted: 25 August,all,Nitestrike776,"Definitely a fun game to play with friends. It presents an interesting mix of card abilities and RPG elements. The combat and quest systems are entertaining and give a nice fresh feel when you play multiple games. The micro transactions, while not the best thing in the world, seem to be for just vanity elements, not pay-to-win type things. Overall it seems to be alot of fun, with great art, music, and sound effects.Many of the reviews are complaining about the quests being ""all the way across the map"", which is honestly not that bad. You take turns to get there and try to complete the quest. I think the real issue is people are used to the almost instant gratification of killing a few monsters and completing an objective. This game is planning intensive, so you need to make strategic choices. Another complaint was that choosing one quest eliminates the ability to choose others. This, once again is about strategy. You need to pick your best path to victory, and each quest leads you toward that path in a different way, so of COURSE you need to think carefully about picking one.The combat system RNG is another point of contention people have. You roll an amount of dice based on your combat level and abilities. With 6 options per die, the odds aren't always going to be in your favor, which is why characters that aren't geared for combat shouldn't be picked. Once again, this is a strategy element. If you get items or abilities that benefit combat, you tend to do better. Addidtionally, you can get lucky and manage to defend well in combat, however the balancing factor is that if you end up rolling most of your dice to defend, you don't get to attack very much. Once again, it seems to be mostly complaining by people that don't have a head for strategy."
