,Recommended,290340,18197622,"Posted: 26 September, 2015",all,Valric,"Armello is a computer board game that is simple to learn but is a challange.When I say ""board game"" I mean this has a kind of mario party (but not as friendship ending) feel to it.Basic  DescriptionYou are from a clan and your goal is to KILL THE KING. It's not due to the fact that he was a bad king, but due to the fact that he is being corrupted by a darkness that shall be refered to as ROT. Now as you are taking on quests getting geared up to break in the gates and commit the act of murder, there are other clans that had the same (or Similar) ideas.this game supports 1-4 playersThe ClansWolf- WarriorRabbit- AdventurerRat- RoguesBear- Mages8 Characters (2 per clan)There is 4 ways to winPrestige- gain the most prestige points and let the king die due to the rot (he loses 1 hp each dawn)Regicide- Kill the king (not as easy as one would think)Rot Victory - Gain more rot points than the king then kill the king (if you like a challenge)Banish - gather 4 magic stones and banish the king (still need to break in though)Pros- the game is pretty fast due to the time limit on the kings life when he ""rots away""- the music- the art/graphics (makes me think of some books like Redwall)- Gamplay its easy to learn and I have yet to get bored- Characters each has a very diffrent feel on how to play themCon's- The only complaint I have, is somtimes the board itself will feel a bit like there is little change to it.  Due to limited tile types such as, forests, mountains, magic circles, dungeons and swamp. This is not including the castle because that is always in the middle.What I wish for- Game customization it would be great to have the ability to change some ""rules"" around like give the king more HP for a longer game have more monsters spawn per night or change the size of the board.Of course in my opinion the Pro's out weigh the Cons greatly and this is a great game to play with your friends and has room to expand.So I say pick up your sword and lets kill an insane king!"
