76561198095927502,Not Recommended,290340,33687581,Posted: 20 July,all,jackofyre,"I really wanted to like this game, I mean it's got sylvanian animal characters as heroes and really colourful art and animation that brings the lore to life. However after spending several hours on the game, I can't help but feel that the game is really inbalanced and that lots of times, the game depends more on luck and chance on getting good cards early on than on your skill and management. You will find that winning is easier with some characters and extremely difficult with others.This is a turn-based strategy game that has minimal storyline, with four players trying to win by getting rid of the Corrupted King and ascending the throne. One can do it in four ways, either by slaying the King, gaining prestige while waiting for the King to expire, collecting Spirit Stones or gaining rot and challenging the King. It may seem that there are many routes to victory but winning via Spirit Stones and Rot is really difficult. And victory usually goes to characters that are strong using the Kingslayer or Prestige route.Personally, I'm not much for multiplayer action, so maybe someone who enjoys multiplayer games may have a different viewpoint. I like the world of Armello though, and would really like to see a single player turn-based strategy RPG game with full storyline based on its characters and lore."
