76561198005176189,Recommended,290340,14402029,"Posted: 9 February, 2015",all,Sushi,"If you're a fan of board games and RPGs, this is a must try, especially mage knight the board game, if you ever played that one, then this game has a lot of elements from it, but obviously simplified for everyone to get into.Everything from looks to art is great, except a minor thing which is the animations in battle seem a bit wonky/awkward, but that's just a preference.Now I understand they decided to limit a lot of deep elements of the genre to attract more people, but I do believe a few things need to be considered for the final release:1) A leveling system: Be it in game for the characters, they gain exp for killing enemies/heroes and when they level up they get to pick some character specific skills which they can use once per round etc.  Account level up to show progress of some sort and rewards such as skins or whatever, rather than just earning rings and whatnot.2) A better variety of enemies more than just a crow/ the option to be able to attack kings guards without the need for the kings orders to allow it.3) Introduce elements such as Fire shield or Ice attack which count as 2 swords and needs 2 blocks to block 1 ice attack and such, this might be a little too complex for the general public though.4) More maps, hopefully this is already being thought of/implemented.5) Like someone has suggested, even though the game has 4 routes to take to win the game, everyone ends up going for the prestige route because its the easiest and more beneficial way, they need to somehow balance to improve variety.6) Different game modes, cooperation between 4 players to fight against the map and conquer castles or such and the trickery spells etc could be used by the enemy minions, another one would be a two on two sort of match with the same elements.7) Allow us to buy recruits at cities or settlements with coins or magic depending on their type, seeing as leaving it to RNG doesn't really have a fun feeling to it.Overall this game is great and I'm quite excited to see it in its final form, but for now I think I'll give it a  rest until it's finished. Great job guys, unique experience."
