76561197970899770,Not Recommended,290340,31989225,Posted: 26 May,all,Rocketdog,"I found this game to be very imbalanced.There are multiple win conditions, but one, 'Prestige' rises to the top by playing relatively passively. The other win conditions take an inordinate amount of resources: moves, time, cards, die, etc..., when compared to 'Prestige' - you do not have to invest as much; just finish your quest, maybe kill a couple on-board enemies, and you're set to win, as the other methods are very difficult, relatively speaking.You may see people refer to certain strategies by using certain characters; i.e. ""Thane - get items, equip shields"" to achieve non-Prestige victories, and yes, you can win that way - but it does not offset the other types of investment you have to do against a Prestige win, and it difficult to do repeatedly with the randomness of cards, deck swapping, losing cards etc...Further, adopting these strategies effectively make half the roster of characters useless, as you are actively choosing to select a character that you will inherently do worse with. So at the end of the day, you have a game with 4 real choices when 16 are presented.Basically, this is not as deep of a game as it appears. It is too bad. It looks great. I love the feel. The systems are nice, but not tuned very well. Buyer beware."
