,Recommended,290340,30934833,Posted: 3 April,all,Nox,"A board game in which diverse animals fight to seize the throne held by a dying king affected by the rot. It's a little adventure where you get to go on a journey to either go agains bots or players to fight for survival sort of. It's a fun game even alone you can enjoy it, however it's a bit glitchy at times I had some weird audio issues while playing, online does suffer a bit too. The ways you can win are pretty unbalanced, it's much easier to win certain ways making the rest tedious for no reason. The characters are generally fun to play they have their own perks and play style, I would not recommend buying something else than the extra characters and that is if you really enjoy the game, the rest is cosmetic and not really worth the money in my opinion. So summary, fun game a bit glitchy, if you like board games like these and can look past the glitches go for it it's not that bad."
,Recommended,290340,30936777,Posted: 3 April,all,Souls,"I was introduced to this game by a friend and I fell in love with it from the moment I started playing it. It is a tale of a kingdom's tragic spiral into chaos and the fight to end a king slowly dying upon his throne, sick and twisted by a foul corruption, The story made me feel sorrow and pity towards the denizens of the kingdom because I felt like I could connect to that conflict. ""No matter who wins the struggle for power, the strength of the kingdom is still lost as the bond of those who formed it disipates into the fires of war"".As for the gameplay, it brought back the enthusiasm I had in tabletop RPGs long ago. Everything is easy to understand for beginners, but still provides a challenge to long time players. The choice of characters and their traits actually makes me feel like I could play as any of them with ease and no matter how south things go in a game, there's a way to turn it around thanks to there being multiple ways to win. The constant threat of royal guards, perils set by the king, and corruption kept things interesting every game. Get some friends together and the chaos will ensue as the game gets more intense as the days pass.I know this isn't much to say about the game considering that I love it, but Armello is my go to game when I need to get my mind off of things or when I just feel like playing a game. The story connects to my heart and the gameplay reminds me of the joys back when I played D&D when I was younger. I'm getting everything for this game because the devs definatly deserve the support."
