76561198063402391,Recommended,290340,33391245,Posted: 8 July,all,GoryWriter,"Just got through my first game of Armello (against the AI, should that even matter), and I have to say I'm fairly impressed. Originally, I had decided to close my wallet to this game when I'd heard the Bandits would be locked exclusively to backers and were more powerful than the base 8 characters, giving everyone who hadn't backed at the Bandit tier a blatant handicap. However, with the Bandits available to purchase for $10 (my first intended DLC purchase, with the Usurpers coming after that), I figured now would be a good time to dive in.So, having only finished the tutorial and knowing the different ways to win, actually being released into the realm left me unsure of just what I should do first. Which clan do I like? Which character is the most interesting? How do I want to win? How will I do what I plan to achieve? I enjoy the backstabbery rogue-like appearance of the Rat clan, so I chose to side with them first, with Zosha as my character. My opponents were Amber, River, and Sana, to which I didn't pay much attention or care. I didn't know whether to go for Prestige or Rot, but the game ended up answering that for me, thus beginning my lengthy journey to win the King's ear and his throne upon his (un)natural demise.Things did start fairly poorly, with River having 3 Prestige before I had even finished my second quest, at which point I had considered switching tactics, but I stuck with it. I focused on quests, buffing myself to - at least what I think to be - a fairly decent 8 Fight and 7 Body, at which point I allowed my daggers (and the occasional bit of magic, if I drew the right spell) to earn their keep. My equipment helped as well, ensuring I entered every combat encounter with the odds, even if slightly, in my favor.I bullied River a bit, as she had the King's ear up to this point, but my first actual hero kill went to Sana, who I had burned to a crisp as she only had 1 health. I then waited in the shadows, picking off targets as they limped away from nearly lost fights, and my Prestige continued to grow. In a short time, the King came to me for his royal decrees, and it stayed that way. My daggers and magic made sure of it. 6 Prestige, then 7, then 8. Up, and up, and up it went, killing heroes, saving settlements, and fighting the Rot. However, by now Amber had started to get a little brave, perhaps from the Rot flowing through her, and started attacking the palace with alarming regularity despite losing her life to either a guard or the King himself. With each passing day, the King grew weaker and weaker, and my victory drew closer. When all was said and done, I sat comfortably upon 12 Prestige, far out of anyone's reach, but the assaults on the castle continued.At long last came the night of the second to last day. Just one more sunrise, and victory would be mine! But the walls continued to be assaulted. Amber from the South, River to the West, and Sana to the North. Sana was dealt with quite easily by the guards I had ordered to be summoned, but that left two more targets to worry about. Amber easily broke through the walls within the daylight hour, killing a guard and regaining her strength to a full 7 hearts. She HAD to die. I followed suit as night fell upon the land, setting a perfect ambush but angering the King as I set foot into his domain. I slaughtered that precious little rabbit without so much as a scratch, sending her back to her home for the third time. Sana, once again, fell to the guards before managing to lift a single finger. However, I had forgotten about River. Somehow, she had slipped within the castle's walls with no trouble at all as I chased Amber about. She then stood there, right before the King, and let loose a single arrow, piercing his fragile heart. All my work, the Prestige I had earned, undone in an instant. Perhaps, had I betrayed the King and plunged my dagger into his back, the Rats would have ruled the land. For now, the Wolves shall enjoy their victory, though I do not intend to make the same mistake twice.Simply put, I'm enjoying this quite a bit."
