,Recommended,290340,32020667,Posted: 28 May,all,Howell of the Wolves,"As a fan of tabletop RPG's, boardgames, and card games, I really like this game. I could explain the mechanics, artstyles, variations in playstyle to help you understand why, but I think I'll share a story.I like to grind achievements, I think it leads to some very interesting outcomes that wouldn't happen if you weren't trying to do a certain thing in a certain way. On this one occasion I was trying to get two achievements at once, equip three treasure cards from dungeons, and have three treasure cards and three followers equiped as Amber, a character who has extra luck when exploring dungeons. I play the game, grinding the same two dungeons over and over for these treasure cards, the outcome of which you have no control over, the game just randomly gives you gold, an enemy, or cards, and fighting anyone who comes too close for ♥♥♥♥♥ and giggles. Near the end of the game, I have three followers and two treasure cards, and am in second place because while I'm doing this I'm using cards to kill people and gain ""Prestige"", so that I can try and scrape out a win (prestige is the point system that determines the winner if the game ends before anyone can kill the king). This has lead me to be one Prestige point behind the winner, but its the second to last turn before the game ends, and me failing to get my achievements. On my very last move of this turn I get teleported across the map to another dungeon, because that is one of the possible outcomes of exploring dungeons. The leader, comes for me, but he had to cross across a dungeon tile to get to me, and this randomly spawned an enemy which attacked him, and prevented him from getting to me, and its his last turn so he can't try to get me again. I have two last chances to grind the dungeon, and the first one produces nothing. I do for my last one, I shout ""Praise GabeN"", and roll the dungeon one last time. As you probably suspect I get my treasure card, but not only is it some treasure card, it's the royal banner, which gives me three presige points when I equip it, which places me in the lead. Win the game, I get my achievements, and I laugh my♥♥♥♥♥off.And that's why I really like this game, because only in a game with such a high emphasise on luck can such absurd things happen, which lead to really memorable moments, and a really memorable game."
