76561198010375650,Not Recommended,290340,19595311,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,-DN-,"I would like to start out by saying that the games advertising is pretty misleading about what this game is and is not.I watched the trailer video which makes the game look like you choose a character and as you play the game you get to go on quest and possibly advance though multiple adventures.  Defeat different AI bosses and maps, possibly carry over card/equipment onto other adventure and so on.Then I read that they are marketing this game as a ""table top game""(printed on their own web page)  which I am a huge fan of and have been playing for many decades.  The only way I have ever played table top games... is with other players.. usually in the same room.. usually at the same table.. ""sigh"".  Now this is where the very misleading part comes into play...  This game has no table top functionality in regards to being able to play with other players as you would with a ""table top game"".Okay so maybe they shipped the game early and they are going to add the ""table top"" into the ""game"" with a patch or update.  Nope they said they did not design their ""table top"" game to be ""table top"" friendly.  ""Sigh""So back to the trailer video...  In the video watching example play is actually the into series to the game.  So as you watch the trailer and expect to go on different adventures on different boards.. with different characters and win conditions.. different bosses.. randomized turn orders etc etc... what you get is...Set player turns, players vs AI player 1 will always go first.. the three other AI characters will go after you and they will always capture you cities on the night turn before dawn.  If you play the game you will soon realize how unbalanced that is.Computer AI will use cards against you as the player even if the same card played against an AI player is either (A) in the lead or (B) more dangerous to them geographically speaking on the map.*Example : computer AI plays a card that does -2 health spell, there are two possible targets.  (A) player that has 4 health 2 squares away on a tile of no importance, or (B) computer AI with 2 health 2 squares away, on their own quest location, and has killed the card player previous 3 times.*What happened:  {Comp playerX} plays spell on {playerY} does (-2) hps (4-2=2hps left), {Comp playerX} moves 2 squares and attacks {Comp playerZ} that is sitting on his quest tile, CompX has 4 hps, CompZ has 2 hps.  CompX has far superior cards and kills CompX by a land slide.  If CompX played his spell vs the other AI on his quest tile he would of been able to complete his quest and not die.  It is as if the AI was programmed to use all hostile cards VS the player first regardless of who best the card should be played in their personal interest.Okay so the AI is terrible... Who needs AI when you can play with friends so no problem.. wait.. oh I forgot you can not play with you're friends.Well you can play with some people.. over the Internet at least.. so lets hit that que button...  30 minutes later you are still in que.So that does not really work either.So what does work...  The into the game works.  You can load it up... get introduced to four of the characters one by one in their own mini adventures.. and well.. It is actually really good.  In fact its so refreshing you think, If they made the whole game this way,  The money spent would have actually been for what you were expecting.The upside to this game is the art.  If you want to play something for a couple hours.. get lost in its ambiance, get some steam achievements and then uninstall it once you realize that theres literally nothing left in the game you haven't seen or done then this games for you.I got it on sale and for the couple hours played it was similar to going to a summer movie... Not a lot story, shiny bits in between, and after its over you kinda wished you waited to see it on TV and kept the money in you're pocket.Maybe if they make the game into what it was marketed as It will be worth it in the future, but ""as is"" I regrettably have to say its an unistall waiting to happen."
