76561198135865194,Not Recommended,290340,35425954,Posted: 2 October,all,SarcasticHamSandwich,"Not worth its weight in gold.Rarely do I ever give bad reviews to games, mainly because the effort in which was placed into them needs at least a small hat-tip, but, bloody hell, this was not worth the twenty dollars I spent.Critiques:- The prologue misled me, which is perhaps the strongest of my irritations. I thought that this was to be a role-playing board game, where, at each map, you were given a plot scenario and you would have to fight your way through quests and competing players to win, thereby reaching the next map, and then the next, moving onto a strange story until you finally got to fight against the lion king at the final map. This was exactly how the prologue acted out for you. You played different characters, achieving different goals until the map dimmed out and you were warped to a different character. I was invested. I was interested.- The ACTUAL game... is nothing like this. There are no new maps. It's the same map (though you can switch between seasons), with the same characters, all striving for the same goal: kill the king or cure him. You know Candy Land? How the setting, the plot, the characters never change? This is basically Candy Land.- There is no plot. Not an ounce of interesting clan dimensions or rivalries. You can fight against your own clan if you want. Nothing makes sense. There's no substance in this game.- The 3D models of the characters are... ah, for lack of a better word, ugly. The 2D profile pictures look marvelous, but when you zoom in on their 3D modeled faces, it's hideous.- The AI makes no sense. Most of the time, it feels like everyone is after you. Everyone seems to be able to bypass trickeries except for you, and despite its ""randomized"" choices, they do their damnedest to focus at you.- Characters are unbalanced. Some are abhorishly overpowered, with dice as far as the eye can see, whilst some only have two or three at their disposal, making combat near-impossible.- It is so damn hard to get inside that stupid castle to cure the king with the spirit orbs. Not only is it littered with traps and guards, the king himself won't let you cure him.Praises:- The prologue could not have been more engaging. I'm still mad that it misled me, though.- The 2D art style was beautiful to look at. I loved both the flat-colored images as well as the painted portraits.- The overall world had so much potential. Animal clans fighting against each other was amazing to watch, and reminded me of Redwall.I haven't tried the multiplayer version of the game, but I'm not wont to do so. This game is frustrating, and its story isn't captivating enough to keep you focused on your objectives. It wasn't worth the twenty dollars, and I regret giving it away."
