,Recommended,290340,24152756,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,Valentine,"Armello  10/10     After playing 5 online matches and winning only one I strongly feel Armello is a thrilling, fun to play turn based strategy with RNG dice and cards, neat animations and captivating gameplay.  You can lose miserably and still have lots of fun.           You pick one of a cast of characters who have various starting stats and passive abilities and then level them up through quests placed on the map as the king in the middle slowly dies.  The quests and various other activities like defeating players and monsters on the map give you prestige, the player with the highest prestige if the king dies of the curse wins the game, if someone kills the king and survives they win the game.There's gold, magic, prestige, the stats, the cards (Equipment, spells, trickery cards and companions.) you can equip 3 equipment cards which usually cost you gold.    The stats are fight(dice in combat.) body (health maximum.) Wit (card maximum and Peril resist) and Spirit (magic pool refresh value)  There is stealth based on certain conditions like which character you are, what tile you're in and what equiptment you might have.  Combat is resolved with dice and cards both.There is a really low learning curve, but lots of tactics, and it's easy to make a poor choice until you get used to the game which adjusts the general new player curve to about medium.   The game so far is pretty much meant for multiplayer competitive play, you can play single player while you're searching for a multiplayer match, much like other games of simular orientation.10/10  for it's genre, I don't give 10/10 lightly, i don't take the time to review a game unless i am insanely impressed with the budget + quality ratio."
