,Recommended,290340,33446426,Posted: 10 July,all,Karegador,"I've seen reviews that call the game broken, for various reasons. However, I have yet to experience those issues.The game is such where no two characters are created equal, giving them each different play styles but victory is equally possible.Yes the otter bandit is tough but maintaining it requires that you maintain a high bounty, which is easily countered with a reprieve card.Further more, strategic questing allows you to build up your stats. To that end one should never choose a quest purely on the loot, you may take a quest and choose the resolution that does not require the test, simply to raise their stats.The game is very involved, gorgeous, and a 10 out of 10."
