76561198131559915,Recommended,290340,25260715,"Posted: 30 August, 2016",all,aringt,"First, I am terrible at writing. Most of my reviews are not very well written, so don't expect J.R.R. Tolkinesk embelishments.I have been playing this game since it came out quite some time ago and have lavishly enjoyed playing it! I have a fondness of games with animals in them and this is no exception. In fact, it has been a joy to engage in this fun little computerized board game.I really like the ""Disney"" quality animation with the charaters and the beautiful set up of the ""board"" landscape. It is very intuitive and you can easily learn the game play very quickly! Especially when you start it with playing the ""Prologue"" which helps teach you the movements and plays from the point of each of the four main characters.To sum Armello up, it's exactly what I mentioned above; a board game. Not a RPG like The Elder Scrolls games or World of Warcraft or Final Fantasy game series, eventhough it has some RPG-like game play. The character you play is a computer animated game peice you play. It moves a certain amount of board spaces and interacts with whatever is in that board space it lands in.Addition, like a boardgame, it is random. It gives you a random set of cards and a random set of plays and no two plays are alike. You have dice that you roll for your battles or for removing ""Perils"" that you enter into. The cards, also, give you some leverage if you have the right cards in your hand. The type of cards that you recieve are by chance and you can never tell what types (in the three tiers that you can select) of cards you will be given when you pick them. If you get to challenge the King you have three types of victories you can perform. They are ""Battle,""""Spirit,"" and ""Rot."" There is one more type of victory you can obtain without challenging the King and that is a ""Prestige"" victory. As far as I have played this game, a Prestige victory is the easiest to obtain, while the Rot victory is the hardest.With that, the game is awesome a lot of fun to play. The AI of the ""Heros"" that you don't play is (in my opinion) astounding. They act as if they are run by an individual person because their moves are so unpredictable. They can attack or choose what to do as if they had a true mind and conciousness of their own!The board's artwork is stunningly gorgious and the changes of the day and seasons are nice additions.The UI is, also, very intuitive and can easily be manuvered.So far, I have not found a ""con"" I can think of that I can even mention against Armello.For those with families, the game is definitely very family friendly. No blood or gore in the game at all. Which is a nice reprieve from games that do.All in all I find this game a real treasure and hope that the company can make it even better and, hopefully they can create a sequil. The game creators have been working very hard to add new features to the game. The DLC ""The Usurpers"" is out now and is actully a fine add-on to the game with four new characters to choose to play as well as some additional items.This game will definitely end up a classic!"
