76561197973833701,Not Recommended,290340,18138228,"Posted: 21 September, 2015",all,baudot,"This is a very clever, very pretty game. The problem is, it's not actually much fun to play.Armello is essentially a computer moderated board game, in the style of a card-driven-narrative game, like Arkham Horror. And like many games in this style, you just kind of fumble through a story, without having much control over it, or without an over-arching plot coming together.The story of Armello is supposed to be a race for the throne among four contendors. But what you actually do as you play is run from quest to quest, with each quest (and all the other action in the game) being settled by randomization elements which feel barely more strategic than a coin flip. All the rich details the game designers poured so much time into have little outcome on the game, or your tactical decisions as you play."
