,Not Recommended,290340,15068647,"Posted: 26 March, 2015",all,Nemikan,"Overall I'd recommend the game.... except that its not worth the current cost so I'm voting NO for the game right now. For a $5 game its awesome, for $25 it won't keep my interest long enough.The game has some interesting mechanics as many people have mentioned. The cards are not as awesome as I expected, the followers I've only seen a few of, and there aren't as many cool effects as I'd like most are just a single modifier in combat.  My biggest complaint is that it seems insanely hard to get into the castle to achive any but the easiest win condition. You must roll on 4 dice (unless you add modifiers or play (burn) cards to ""set"" the results)  4 specific types. If you do not, your turn ends and you must try again the next day. I spent a whole game trying to do that from the start, with +3 dice modifier and failed to do so before the game ended. This fustrates me since I don't see it being multiplayer competitive due to that reason.Battles are very short, a single dice roll and usually end with one or both players dying - defense is so much more important than offense, although the death penalty is very small, just -1 prestige. It adds an interesting element. The map is small, something I didn't realize when browsing through the game before I bought it.All in all, the game has some fun graphics, cool with the heroes being random animals, and a fairly unique game. Once again if it weren't for the cost, I'd recommend it, however it won't keep you interested for a huge amount of time. A nice indie game, not the new CoD."
