76561198063840510,Recommended,290340,18337027,"Posted: 4 October, 2015",all,tyleegoat,"i love this game, but I really think it should have a local/ splitscreen type play. It's super amazing and could only get better with co-op"
,Recommended,290340,19435267,"Posted: 2 December, 2015",all,Vi,"TLDR: Recommended ONLY if it is on sale for 50% or so, or if you are a fan of playing board games with family/friends. Very pretty game that can be quite engaging the first times you play it. However, stay clear if you are not a fan of ""luck based"" games, if you just want to singleplay to play it everyday AND if you expect to win every session. That won't happen.Full review:It can be horribly unfair, or it can be downright cake walk, like a lot of board games out there this game will really test your luck.Sometimes you may start out with a lot of gold, thus you then would base your play method on playing a lot of trick cards to troll the other Heroes while you focus on getting prestige or something else.Other times you may get a very rare and strong equipment cards, to the point where (as it happened to me on one session) in a few turns you could get a combo that gives you 9 shields at the start of every battle, making you pretty much unkillable in that way (they can still kill you with spells/traps/etc however).And other times... well, you may get killed before the next dawn over and over. Traps, unlucky dice rolls, getting quest objectives that are on the other side of the map of where you are... and maybe then the King and his ""favorite"" Hero will decide on next turn to strip you off all your cards or gold! Fun times indeed.No single game session is the same, which is actually a good thing since it won't feel repetitive too fast gameplay-wise, and the game uses a card system for your items and spells, and they all come with animated pictures which are overall beautiful to look at. Overall, the art and design of this game is its best aspect in my opinion.Unfortunately, it does get repetitive on other areas. For example, the game is really lacking on type of ""tiles"" for the map (maybe something like water tiles which take 2 AP but make you immune to spells? or maybe something like a Dungeon-Fort that awards you with an item/card if you manage to defeat a strong enemy in it? just a few examples out of my mind right now), and on map diversity as well, with there only being 2 map types (normal and winter, which are only for asthetic porpuses), it really gets dull fast and it really feels like more could have been done with these aspects.Length of each session is what I believe ""enough"". The game has a sort of turn limit since each day the King will get weaker and weaker until his health is depleted which ends the game session unless someone kills/banishes the king before that. This usually takes about 20 turns or so and overall each session tends to last about 2-3 hours depending on how fast players play their turns. After playing it for a while (say, 7-8 full game sessions) it will probably become too repetitive on its visuals, but gameplay should still feel fun and fresh every time you play, especially if you play with other people rather than the AI.Nice game with evident flaws, but nothing that cannot be polished on future updates. And even if they aren't, its still a good game to play once every now and then especially with other people as you would with any board game."
76561198062039191,Not Recommended,290340,19422175,"Posted: 1 December, 2015",all,Sir poezer,"I have picked this game up in a sale, because it looked like a great game. When I first started it up I was very excited. The music and the artwork were amazing. The animations were smooth and looked nice and the characters were diverse and looked unique.After a few games though I started noticing a rather agitating patern. Almost every game I played ended the same way, a prestige victory. The game is so chance based, in both the rolls and cards that it is incredibly difficult to get enough good gear and stats to defeat the king. Not just that, but try to go for the spirit stone or rot victory and it becomes even harder since you need to collect even more stuff.The dice roll mechanic looks like a fun idea, but with a 1/2 chance of getting an attack and 1/6 chance of getting a defence, with the possibility of getting infinite attacks with the dice-explosion, it becomes incredibly difficult to stay alive. Even with 8 dice you can still easily see yourself losing against 4, which can be infuriating.The world looks amazing and I love the characters, but with every aspect of the game being affected by chance takes away part of the fun. It's a real shame, because the game looks amazing and the music is great. If it wasn't so heavily influenced by chance it would be a way better game than it is now."
