76561198005691959,Recommended,290340,20820054,"Posted: 28 January, 2016",all,"Sequester Grundleplith, M.D.","This game may or may not be to your tastes, but if this is the sort of thing you're into you'll have a blast.  The artwork and music are beautiful, and they lend a lot of weight to the world and characters (although the lore really is just a flavorful backdrop; don't expect to get sucked in by the story or anything.)  It's a digital board game with some light RPG elements, where your goal is to succeed the current king of Armello, who is suffering from a magical corruption that is driving him mad and slowly killing him.  There are multiple paths to victory, which means there's usually a way for you to pursue victory even if your first choice doesn't work out.  It's not enough to go after the king, though.  You need to be laying traps, making opportunistic attacks, and generally just screwing over the other players as much as possible.Combat in the game is extremely lethal, and there is a heavy element of randomness to the whole game, both of which can cause some frustration; both of those factors do make the game more exciting, though.  Think of it like the board game that it is, not a competitive esport - sometimes victory just goes to whoever rolls best, and that's okay.  You're just there to have a good time."
76561198080910417,Recommended,290340,20706969,"Posted: 23 January, 2016",all,grangle1,"This is a really thematic, enjoyable game to play.  There are three (though the devs say four) different ways to win, combined with eight playable characters (minus the Bandit Clan), which makes for a nice variety of strategy and playstyle options.  If playing against the AI the game is on the easy side (I've only ever lost to the AI once), so at least for me, the challenge comes not from winning but figuring out the best way to maximize my winning potential with the setup I choose.  The randomly generated environments are another nice touch for interesting gameplay and almost infinite replay value.  Visually the game looks beautiful and fits the theme very well, and the music is good, providing a nice audio background.  It's not too exciting but it gets the job done.  Games last about an hour, which is just right for this kind of game; not too short, but not so long it gets burdensome, and if you don't have enough time to get a round in you can save and pick it up later.The game isn't perfect, though.  While I am a big fan of board games in general and this is great for a video board game, it's just the nature of video board games that you're going to spend a lot of time waiting for the other players to take their turn.  It doesn't help that again, if you're playing against AI, even if you're set to fast AI turns and watching the dice roll during battles, the AI players' turns can be boring and take a long time to resolve.  As for multiplayer, the lack of local hotseat multiplayer is a big let-down.   The last potential negative I see is something I don't mind, given that I do like these kinds of games, but others may be annoyed by it:  you do have stats that you build and quests you go on to increase them, but luck remains a sizeable factor in the outcome of the game:  dice are rolled and cards are drawn, and while you can increase your maximum hand of cards or number of dice you have in battle or during trap tests, if the dice don't roll your way or someone else gets the awesome card you're looking for, you may still potentially lose the game.  Part of the strategy and fun for me is figuring out ways to work around that, and it's not too hard to do so and still win, but it can get frustrating when you're trying to win in a certain way in order to unlock a ring or amulet.This game is already great fun, and I would definitely recommend it, though I do see great potential for expanisions in the future to make it even better, adding characters, cards and/or different mechanics and scenarios.  If they do add more expansions (I know there is the Bandit Clan but I don't have it) I'm definitely going to pick it up!  Here's hoping for more in the future!"
