76561198052903831,Recommended,290340,30825481,Posted: 29 March,all,Mirri,"I enjoy this game quite a bit. I've play roughly equal amounts of single player and multplayer games. It's fun to get the mystery chests from multiplayer games but I still think it's worth the money even if you just play single player. The AI isn't bad, and I've won and lost games against it. If you like strategic boards games in general, this is a good one to venture online with. I usually play one game at a time, maybe two, and time varies but I'd say between half an hour and one hour to finish the game. Turns are set so there is a cap on how long a game can be.The visuals are delightful. The board is pretty and the character movements are smooth. It can take a bit of waiting while NPC's resolve their own rolls (which you can choose to watch or not). I'm often spending that time looking through my cards and deciding what I might want to do for my turn. The music is not obstusive, and makes a good ambience for the game.Just the Vanilla game for me right now, I don't have the DLC but I plan to get it. Right now I find the vanilla characters and options are enough to enjoy the game, and so far I don't find myself being drawn to specific characters or playstyles, or feeling like any one character has a heavy advantage over any other. With several ways to win the game, it allows for more options of play."
