76561198035774240,Recommended,290340,31093175,Posted: 12 April,all,Sir SpanksAlot,"I promised myself that if I played 200 hours of this game, that I'd leave a review.1st off, let me say that I personally hate the binary system steam forces you to use - you either recommend this game, or you do not.While I do personally love Armello, I'll be the first to shove an♥♥♥♥♥♥in my face and say that this game isn't for everyone. If you hate digital board games, where people might literally spend 5 minutes on their turn, then DO NOT get this game.But if you like outwitting your opponents (albeit there's a rather hefty component of luck involved), if you don't mind waiting for your turn, and you do like board games, Armello is for you.I personally love the 'game-of-throne'/'redwall'-esque mechanics of the game. The artwork is second to none, and is perhaps best described as Disney-meets-anime.As for gameplay, I love the varied victory paths available to the player. It means that no matter how cr4ppy a start you may have, you will ALWAYS have a decent chance at victory. This is precisely what makes the last few rounds of Armello so darn exciting. The heroes available to the player feel very balanced, and are all geared towards a very distinct playstyle - however, they are by no means restricted to be played in a one dimensional manner.That being said, I do have my complaints. Suffice to say that I own a powerful gaming laptop, the incompatibility of Armello with windows 10 makes playing it like having a papercut on your♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ It's not going to stop you from getting the deed done, but it is rather unpleasant. The framerate is choppy, the game does crash occasionally, and it consumes about 40% of my 8gbs of RAM. That being said, it is a problem the devs are aware of, and I do believe that they are working on it.Another complaint I have is the inability to reconnect into a game. For instance, should the game crash due to the aforementioned reason, it automatically counts as a defeat. And do note that the game DOES lag-out for all parties occasionally.Overall, I do enjoy playing Armello. It's a great game. And I personally am okay with the shortcomings of it as I can imagine how difficult it must be for such a small dev team to keep this game running."
