76561197997794666,Recommended,290340,29026670,Posted: 4 January,all,Tikigod,"I love this board game.  Great visuals and lighting effects.  I really enjoy the artwork and unique storyline.  I enjoy the varieties of cards you can collect, along with the attention to detail that was put into each of the animations.  The gaming style has many different strategies, tactics, and angles to think about while you play.   Each character you choose has a very unique style that changes the way you think and plan out your strategy.  Its like playing a different game with each character you use.While waiting for multiplayer match, the game allows you to play single player game, then alerts you with a popup to join when your match is ready.  You do get to unlock unique items to play in future games (dice with unique bonus symbols for fighting, rings with perks, and badges that give you bonuses to certain character traits starting off) These are unlocked by collecting chests and keys in multiplayer matches.  You do not have to purchase keys to unlock chests like in other games with this feature.  You get to win, collect, and unlock these items for free which is nice.  I did however purchase the DLC expansions because I enjoy the amount of artwork that was put into this game and want to support the developer and see where they go with future titles.I look forward to seeing more cards and animations added to the game.  The cards themselves  are very entertaining.The game is very replayable and doesn't get boring quickly. (although, I wish the external movement animations and watching other players battle was a little more interesting)If you like board games, with a bit of depth, and deck building (per game) I definately recommend this title.ProsUnique StorylineGreat Artwork, Animations, Lighting, and EffectsVery ReplayableEverything you win in multiplayer you get to unlock without having to buy more into the game with micro transactions.  (The micro transaction type of purchasing model just annoys me)Best looking cards and hand drawn animations that I have seen in a game.Lots of depth to Strategy, Tactics, and multiple levels of PlanningMultiple ways to win a game.Unique characters each with different play styles.All traits are not fixed and can be improved by taking quests, acquiring cards, and winning battles.ConsDefault gameplay can feel fairly long.  However they have added options to tweak the speed and pace to your choosing.  You will come out of this game wondering what happened to the last two to three hours of your night.  But, you will enjoy playing it.I felt the price is a bit high (to purchase the title and all the dlc content at once in the bundle package). Its kinda hard to convince friends to purchase a board game for this price (especially one that contains a fantasy genre with enchanted animals that come from a magical forest).  I am willing to purchase all of the content because I appreciate the artwork and overall design of the game.   But, alot of my friends are cheap,  and don't like to buy anything if its over the $15-$20 range.  I myself, don't like to gift to people that are cheap, and that are ok with letting artists and programmers starve.  So, I am kinda stuck in an infinate Catch 22 scenerio.Its hard explaining to others what exactly you are doing when you are caught playing a game with lots of happy colors and magical creatures."
76561198050263083,Recommended,290340,28996169,Posted: 3 January,all,THE PWNER,"Gameplay 8/10Graphics 9/10Audio 8/10Cons:-Slighlty unfair ranking system-A fair time of waitingArmello is not your average strategy game due to the unique winning conditions and constantly changing board events. In this game you will play as one of the four animal clans seeking to take down the king of Armello who has been corrupted by a evil known as rot, yet there are three other players that also wish to take down the king and steal his throne for themselves. All these players are pushed into one RANDOMLY generated board composed of varying hex tiles that take effect upon the player ( Ex. Moving into a swamp causes you to lose a life while moving into a spirirt circle gives you a life). I personally enjoy the gameplay for there is a hint of cut throat required over multiplayer and in fact many ways to win the game which gives every player a path to take towards victory. The random generation of the board along with the King's Acts that are determined by a player makes no two games alike as players are trying to win the game through their own preffered path. Graphics in the game are rather stunning as the cards actullay have fine detailed art that actually moves upon hvoering over said card. Games can last up to about a hour or more, yet the graphics are thankfully easy on the eyes as you play hours on end. Audio is nothing really to praise nor spit on. The CONS vary in severity to player to player and may effect whether or not you wish to buy this game. Games can last for long hours and demands that you idly wait for your turn as other players take their lengthy turn which can lead you to becoming rather bored after skimming over your cards and planning your next turn if it ever comes. A Multiplayer issue is the ranking system where you maybe a mere level one and end up being paired up with a rank 5 player which seems a bit unfair or poor ranking. I would reccomend this game to those who are fine waiting for their turns over a long lengthy game and are willing to put in time to play a whole game. I give Armello 9/10 Spirit Stones"
