76561198005400484,Recommended,290340,29802633,Posted: 9 February,all,DoominaBottle,"See My Review Video Below:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J1RQEB_GFLUThree Parts Board Game, one part Fantasy RPG Armello is a beautiful and addictive digital board game created by League of Geeks.While there are some worrying DLC practices regarding the game the price of the core game is rather decent and furthermore has a solid and reliable single player as well as online multiplayer.TLDW:Pros:Low Price for core game, often on sale.Easy to understand and entertaining tutorials.Simple to pick up, deceptively fast gameplay, Single player games take on average 30 minutes and online 1 hour.Beautiful cinematics and overall artstyle with hits of a deeper story.Atmospheric music and sound effects.Decent AI though it is explotable.Unlocks available in single player and regardless of a win or loss.Multiple victory conditions which can allow players to always feel they have a chance of success.Each game is different due to the variations available and the ability to craft custom games.Character each have prefered playstyles but can adapt to any victory type.Steam Cards and Achievements.Cons:Cosmetic DLC rather costly or has distastleful requirements leading to resentment in the community.It is not always clear why a player doesn't have a chance to respond to Perils.Multiplayer is partly unstable at this time with occasional connection drops, though AI take over dropped players should anything happen to a player's connection, there is zero ability to reconnectKey and Chest drops only available in multiplayer.Lack of hardware interface options. (This can be a pro for those wishing a simple setup)The Combat can make turns long in multiplayer.Bot Farming: Due to high cost of cosmetic drops players have been know to join multiplayer and go afk just to earn drops however the reporting system is eay and should be encouraged.Unlike in the tutorials the followers offer no banter which is a bit disappointing and reduces their character a little.Lack of game modes, an adventure or story mode similar to the tutorial or a team V.S. would of been a nice edition.Music can be a little too calm and becomes unnoticeable after a while, consider having your own fantasy playlist on standby.No modding.Final verdict: Worth the price as a solid digital board game, I recommend picking up the core game and Usurpers Hero Pack while on sale but ignore the overpriced cosmetics."
