,Recommended,290340,29679047,Posted: 3 February,all,BooBooKittyFace,"What's this game about?First off, this is a board game. It's a very fun and charming board game that is partially luck based.!!.If you aren't in to luck based games, this isn't for you.!!You pick a hero from four different clans: Wolf, Bear, Rabbit, and RatYou all take a turn to draw cards from 3 decks: Item, Magic, Trickery(you get more cards based on your Wit stat)You also start out with a certain amount of gold and magic(Magic is gained from increasing the Spirit stat)You use that gold to equip items or play tricks on other heroes, and of course you use the magic to cast spells.When in battle, both parties get dice to roll(The higher your Fight stat the more dice you start with. Items can affect how many dice you or your opponent have.)Your only goal is to become the King of Armello. There are four different ways to win: Rot, Prestige, King Slayer, and Spirit Stones.DLC/SkinsSome may be saying the developers are greedy by adding dice and hero skins, but the dice sets are free to win through multiplayer during the time they are out. Otherwise you can buy them at a very cheap price in the community store. Also these skins have no actual effect on the game, because they are purely cosmetic. The hero skins come at a bit of a steeper price but games cost money to make and you don't HAVE to buy these skins.COSMETICS AREN'T MANDATORY TO BUY!I personally bought the Usurpers DLC to add more variety to the heroes I have to choose from and I love them. They all come with a unique set of abilities and their own ring. Those four heroes really add to this game!What did I like about this game?This game has some really cute characters, like my favorite River Wolf.It's similar to older board games like Heroscape.You can play with friends or by yourself if you really prefer singleplayer.You recieve either a key or a chest at the end of every multiplayer match, and those chests contain Free Dice!! You don't have to win the match to get them either.I wouldn't pass this game up just because there are some mixed reviews."
