76561198095840134,Recommended,290340,33699999,Posted: 21 July,all,Cheap Shot Nate,"This is a fun board game, with two win conditions. Kill the king (three ways to do that), or have the most prestige when the king inevitably dies. There is RNG in this game...it uses dice, and the hex based board is random (with some rules to the layout) but you can play around it, and sometimes it's best to change strategy when the build you wanted to make goes screwy. Every character feels different even the ones that play similarly have there own nuances. The biggest issue with the game as of this patch is the never ending turns, the turns are supposed to end in 60 seconds for a standard multiplayer match, but unfortunately the last four games I've played have ran into one player not being able to end their turn. I've had it happened to me 2 of the 4 times, and I believe it might be linked to some of the characters. I've reported it everytime (that it let me) so now all we can do is wait for it to be fixed, and it will be, this game regularly gets hot fixed. So over all it's a good game, but you might want to wait until next patch to buy it.EDIT: And the bugs I have been encountering have just being patched away. :) Just had a wonderful back and forth game with no bugs."
,Recommended,290340,33845150,Posted: 27 July,all,Mouritzeen,"Armello is a great game built on an RNG system that you will sometimes love but will most of the time you will hate it.The way Armello represents the RNG is straight forward, suns hit in the day, moons hit in the night, swords always attack, shields always defend, worm die do nothing, wylds attack and rolls another die unless you become corrupted then the wyld and worm switch ability. The RNG is all presented in a very nice looking screen where you throw your customizable die with your cursor. The biggest issue is that you will often find yourself in a situation where you rolled full attack like your opponent, and you both die or even just throw five worms while you have zero rot, this happens far more than it should, even if you have the proper equipment.The game is otherwise good, great even. The aesthetic is beautiful, the characters have great quotes, ""What's harder X? Your skull or my shield,"" the quest are good, and when the RNG is even slightly charitable, the game is a blast even if you don't win. Just remember that it isn't over until there is a new king, so many times has someone been so sure of victory I walk into the castle and become King."
