76561198038416288,Recommended,290340,34258874,Posted: 15 August,all,Articulatefish,"A delightful computer board game with strong gameplay, colourful board and card designs and nice animations.You play the role of one of the characters belonging to an Animal Clan in the Kingdom of Armello, working to overthrow the corrupted King Lion and becoming its new ruler. The game is always 4 players, and has 4 different win conditions which one way or another involve the death of the old King.The game is easy to get into while retaining depth in the combinations of items, spells, trickery, follower and treasure cards that you acquire over the course of the game. The characters all have different abilities and interact with one another on their quest while adventuring across Armello to prepare to take down the King.Would definitely recommend buying the game, it's great to play with friends and is generally completed in under an hour. The DLCs do enrich the way you play the game with new characters but the game works perfectly well without them, and the game is compatible to play with others regardless of owned DLCs.One final note is that randomness plays a heavy part in the game, the makers of Armello make no secret of this fact! If you find randomness frustrating there are ways to play around it, but you will generally not do as well as those that take the bigger risks.Every single player is still in with a chance to win right at the end, which actually is a positive feature of the game because it incentivises you not to give up!"
